        "timestamp": "2019-04-29 20:07:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I see you're picking up the latest images change in drools and\n > engine I made, hopefully will work.\n > \n > Question, upgrading to the docker version, does it solve the\n > problem then with manually needing to pull the policy-common image\n > manually as I had in in the other csit parallel review.   At least\n > that's what it looks like.  Can you confirm?   Or what problems\n > does it solve to upgrade the docker version for my own\n > understanding?\n\nI am not sure if it would resolve the problem of manually pulling the docker image problem. \n\nI pushed these changes because of conflict between pip docker-py and pip docker. I saw this issue on other CSITs with failing docker-compose. It worked over there. I was waiting for you to finalize your changes to resolve \"timeout\" issue. Once your fix is in and hopefully latest images are being pulled I think this should work.",
